post_text:
Good Evening Gateway Families. This message is to inform you that the Gateway Regional Board of Education voted this evening to revise the Reopening plan to begin the school year through remote instruction only until at least October 13th. This decision is pending Department of Education approval.

At the September 30 meeting, the Board of Education will reassess the situation and make a decision regarding future instructional plans. Please know that this decision was not made lightly and we understand how this will affect your family. We thank you for your understanding and patience during this difficult time.

School will begin on September 10, 2020. Fully remote instruction will follow the Gateway Regional All Virtual schedule. Students will be expected to log-in for live instruction for their classes. Links for courses will follow. Please refer to the Hybrid/Virtual Instructional Expectations document for more information regarding academic expectations.

Tomorrow’s 7th grade orientation will continue as scheduled. More information and details on the revised plan will follow soon.

Please note that the Gateway front office staff will be available on Monday (6/22) and Tuesday (6/23) from 10am-2pm in order to collect GRHS materials as well as assist in distributing locker contents and Grade 8 graduation materials. Everything dropped off MUST be clearly labeled with the student's name and current grade level.

IF YOU STILL HAVE NOT RETURNED YOUR CHROMEBOOK and would like to pay the annual user fee to keep it for the summer please click the following link. If the annual user fee is not collected and the device is not returned for summer storage we will have to deactivate the device for the summer. This process will begin July 1.

MySchoolBucks - https://www.myschoolbucks.com/ver2/prdembd?ref=ZZHACLKPEP01228_ZZJ6F5TY4Y0Q842

After these dates all drop off and collections will be by appointment only.

Thank you for your cooperation in this matter.

Be safe.

post_text:
Congratulations to Grace Brokenshire who has made it to national semi finalist status as a US Presidential Scholar for Career and Technical Education.

Betsy DeVos will announce finalists in May. Out of 5,600 students across the nation, Grace is one of only 620 to make it this far!

Grace was a G2C environmental engineer intern for Maser Consulting and has committed to Lafayette College in the fall for Civil and Environmental Engineering.

We have no doubt that our planet is better off with Grace working on it.

#gatorstartcareerstar Women in STEM #stemwomen

post_text:
The entire Gateway community is feeling the effects of our new reality of remote learning. The seniors of the Class of 2020 are also feeling the disappointment and anxiety of losing time with their teachers, coaches, friends and administrators in the halls of Gateway before moving onto their bright futures outside of Gatorland.

This week virtual spirit week is dedicated to the senior class, so that they can know that the entire Gateway community is behind them and supporting them! The Class of 2020 leadership has taken over virtual spirit week and they would love the entire Gateway community to participate to show their support for the class of 2020!

When you are posting make sure to use the hashtag #grhsvirtualspiritweek and tag the Gateway Facebook Page, @2020.gators and @grhs_student_council depending on the platform.

Thank you for showing your support!

UPDATE: We wanted to let you know that we understand there is a high level of concern regarding recent events but we are also seeing and hearing a lot of inaccurate and false information being circulated which is creating additional alarm.

Please be assured the district has followed the code of conduct regarding threats being made against students and the school. In coordination with local law enforcement, we reaffirm that all steps are being taken to ensure student safety. Due to student privacy laws we are unable to provide further information at this time.

post_text: UPDATE:: On 10/26/2019 Woodbury Heights Police Department received information in regards to threatening social media posts made by a Gateway High School Student. Woodbury Heights Police conducted a detailed investigation and has taken all steps to ensure that Gateway High School can safely open as scheduled. On 10/27/2019 a Gateway student was arrested and charged with Creating False Public Alarm in connection with the social media posts.

post_text: This is Gateway Regional School District. We wanted to let you know we have been made aware of a threatening social media post. The district has been working with local police to conduct an investigation. Gateway is scheduled to be open for school tomorrow and we will update you if we have any further information.

As a reminder to students::

Grades 7-11 > Will report directly to their homeroom in the morning.

Grades 7-11 > Students will need their charged chromebooks.

Seniors > attending career day will need to park in the back staff parking lot.

Seniors > must report directly to Ms. Powell (near HS Gym) to check in and have your attendance taken.

DUE TO THE INCLEMENT WEATHER CONDITIONS MS BAND AND CHORUS HAVE BEEN CANCELLED FOR TODAY.

THERE WILL NOT BE ANY LATE BUS RUNS AFTER SCHOOL TODAY. ALL STUDENTS SHOULD LEAVE THE BUILDING AT 2:37PM AND TAKE THEIR REGULAR BUS HOME.

PLEASE BE SAFE GOING HOME TODAY IN THIS UNEXPECTED WINTER STORM.

THANK YOU.

Just a reminder, Chromebooks are now being distributed to all grade levels. In order to receive your chromebook for the year we must collect the annual $25 user fee. If you have not yet made a payment, you can do so online by clicking the My School Bucks link on Gateway's website. Checks made out to Gateway Regional School District and cash will also be accepted. Please make sure your child's full name is on the memo line of any check.

If you have already submitted the payment, please disregard this message.
